{"title_page": "Serie A (men's handball)", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox handball league\n| logo       = \n| pixels     = \n| country    = [[Italy]]\n| confed     = [[European Handball Federation|EHF]]\n| rank       = 33\n| founded    = 1969\n| teams      = 14\n| relegation = [[Serie A2 (men's handball|Serie A2]]\n| levels     = 1\n| domest_cup = \n| confed_cup = [[EHF Cup]]<br>[[EHF Challenge Cup]]\n| champions  = [[SSV Bozen Loacker]]\n| season     = \n| most successful club = [[Pallamano Trieste]] (17 titles)\n| tv         = \n| website    = http://www.figh.it/\n| current    = [[2019\u201320 Serie A (men's handball)|2019\u201320 season]]\n}}\nThe Italian '''Serie A''' is the name of the highest level [[team handball|handball]] league of [[Italy]].\n\n== Competition Format ==\n\nThe season has 26 game days (or weeks) and is played as a [[Round-robin tournament]]. At th end of the regular season, the top eight teams qualify for the playoffs, where a best-of-three system is used.\nAt the end of the season, the bottom two finishers are automatically relegated to the second level of the Italian league system, the [[Serie A2 (men's handball)|Serie A2]]. \n\n== 2019/20 Season participants==\n\nThe following 28 clubs compete in the Serie A during the 2016\u201317 season.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- align=center \n! width=280 | Team\n! width=200 | City\n! width=220 | Arena\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[SSV Bozen Loacker]]'''\n|[[Bolzano]]\n|PalaResia\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Pallamano Pressano|Handball Club Pressano]]'''\n|[[Lavis]]\n|Palavis\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Sport Club Meran Handball]]'''\n|[[Merano]]\n|Centro Scolastico Carlo Wolf\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Pallamano Trieste]]'''\n|[[Trieste]]\n|PalaChiarbola\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Cassano Magnago HC]]'''\n|[[Cassano Magnago]]\n|PalaTacca\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Handball Siena]]'''\n|[[Siena]]\n|PalaEstra\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Handball Club Fondi]]'''\n|[[Fondi]]\n|Palasport di Fondi\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[SSV Brixen Handball]]'''\n|[[Bressanone]]\n|Palasport di Bressanone\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Sporting Club Gaeta 1970]]'''\n|[[Gaeta]]\n|Palasport di Fondi\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Junior Fasano]]'''\n|[[Fasano]]\n|PalaZizzi\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Handball Club Conversano]]'''\n|[[Conversano]]\n|Pala San Giacomo\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Handball Sassari]]'''\n|[[Sassari]]\n|PalaSantoru\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[ASV Eppan Handball L\u00f6wen]]'''\n|[[Appiano sulla strada del vino]]\n|Raffeisenhalle\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Pallamano Cologne]]'''\n|[[Cologne, Lombardy|Cologne]]\n|PalaDanti\n\n|-\n|}\n\n==Serie A past champions==\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-4}}\n* 1970 : Buscaglione Roma\n* 1971 : HC Flaminio Genovesi Roma\n* 1972 : CUS Verona\n* 1973 : C.S. Esercito Roma\n* 1974 : HC Rovereto\n* 1975 : HC Rovereto <small>(2)</small>\n* 1976 : Pallamano Trieste\n* 1977 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(2)</small>\n* 1978 : HC Rovereto <small>(3)</small>\n* 1979 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(3)</small>\n* 1980 : HC Rovereto <small>(4)</small>\n* 1981 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(4)</small>\n* 1982 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(5)</small>\n{{col-4}}\n* 1983 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(6)</small>\n* 1984 : HC Scafati\n* 1985 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(7)</small>\n* 1986 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(8)</small>\n* 1987 : CC Ortigia Siracusa\n* 1988 : CC Ortigia Siracusa <small>(2)</small>\n* 1989 : CC Ortigia Siracusa <small>(3)</small>\n* 1990 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(9)</small>\n* 1991 : SSV Brixen Handball\n* 1992 : SSV Brixen Handball <small>(2)</small>\n* 1993 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(10)</small>\n* 1994 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(11)</small>\n* 1995 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(12)</small>\n{{col-4}}\n* 1996 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(13)</small>\n* 1997 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(14)</small>\n* 1998 : Pallamano Prato\n* 1999 : Pallamano Prato <small>(2)</small>\n* 2000 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(15)</small>\n* 2001 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(16)</small>\n* 2002 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(17)</small>\n* 2003 : Handball Club Conversano\n* 2004 : Handball Club Conversano <small>(2)</small>\n* 2005 : SC Merano\n* 2006 : Handball Club Conversano <small>(3)</small>\n* 2007 : Handball Casarano\n* 2008 : Handball Casarano <small>(2)</small>\n{{col-4}}\n* 2009 : Handball Casarano <small>(3)</small>\n* 2010 : Handball Club Conversano <small>(4)</small>\n* 2011 : Handball Club Conversano <small>(5)</small> \n* 2012 : [[SSV Bozen Loacker]]\n* 2013 : [[SSV Bozen Loacker]] <small>(2)</small> \n* 2014 : [[Junior Fasano]] \n* 2015 : [[SSV Bozen Loacker]] <small>(3)</small>\n* 2016 : [[Junior Fasano]] <small>(2)</small>\n* 2017 : [[SSV Bozen Loacker]] <small>(4)</small>\n* 2018 : [[Junior Fasano]] <small>(3)</small>\n* 2019 : [[SSV Bozen Loacker]] <small>(5)</small>\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#e9e9e9\"\n!\n! Club\n! Titles\n! Year\n|-\n|| 1. || Pallamano Trieste || 17 || 1976, 1977, 1979, 1981, 1982, 1983, 1985, 1986, 1990, 1993, 1994, 1995, 1996, 1997, 2000, 2001, 2002\n|-\n|| 2. || Handball Club Conversano || 5 || 2003, 2004, 2006, 2010, 2011\n|-\n|| || [[SSV Bozen Loacker]] || 5 || 2012, 2013, 2015, 2017, 2019\n|-\n|| 3. || HC Rovereto || 4 || 1974, 1975, 1978, 1980\n|-\n|| 5. || CC Ortigia Siracusa || 3 || 1987, 1988, 1989\n|-\n|| || Handball Casarano || 3 || 2007, 2008, 2009\n|-\n|| || [[Junior Fasano]] || 3 || 2014, 2016, 2018\n|-\n|| 8. || SSV Brixen Handball || 2 || 1991, 1992\n|-\n|| || Pallamano Prato || 2 || 1998, 1999\n|-\n|| 10. || Buscaglione Roma || 1 || 1970\n|-\n|| || HC Flaminio Genovesi Roma || 1 || 1971\n|-\n|| || CUS Verona || 1 || 1972\n|-\n|| || C.S. Esercito Roma || 1 || 1973\n|-\n|| || HC Scafati || 1 || 1984\n|-\n|| || SC Merano || 1 || 2005\n|}\n\n==EHF coefficient ranking==\n:''For season 2017/2018''<ref>[http://cms.eurohandball.com/PortalData/1/Resources/3_other_ec/3_download