 play-off group play a elimination round to be the fourth team to reach semifinals. \nIn the play-out round, the last team of each group is relegated.\n\n== 2018/19 Season participants==\n\nThe following 28 clubs compete in the Serie A during the 2016\u201317 season.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- align=center \n! width=280 | Team\n! width=200 | City\n! width=220 | Arena\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[SSV Bozen Loacker]]'''\n|[[Bolzano]]\n|Palestra Gasteiner\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Pallamano Pressano|Handball Club Pressano]]'''\n|[[Lavis]]\n|Palavis\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Sport Club Meran Handball]]'''\n|[[Merano]]\n|Centro Scolastico Carlo Wolf\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Pallamano Trieste]]'''\n|[[Trieste]]\n|PalaChiarbola\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Cassano Magnago HC]]'''\n|[[Cassano Magnago]]\n|Palatacca\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Handball Siena]]'''\n|[[Siena]]\n|PalaEstra\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Handball Club Fondi]]'''\n|[[Fondi]]\n|Palasport di FOndi\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[SSV Brixen Handball]]'''\n|[[Bressanone]]\n|Palasport di Bressanone\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Sporting Club Gaeta 1970]]'''\n|[[Gaeta]]\n|Palasport di Fondi\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Junior Fasano]]'''\n|[[Fasano]]\n|PalaZizzi\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Handball Club Conversano]]'''\n|[[Conversano]]\n|Pala San Giacomo\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Poisportiva Cingoli]]'''\n|[[Cingoli]]\n|PalaQuaresima\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Bologna United Handball Club]]'''\n|[[Bologna]]\n|PalaSavena\n|- bgcolor=ffffe0\n|'''[[Pallamano Cologne]]'''\n|[[Cologne, Lombardy|Cologne]]\n|PalaDanti\n\n|-\n|}\n\n==Serie A past champions==\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-4}}\n* 1970 : Buscaglione Roma\n* 1971 : HC Flaminio Genovesi Roma\n* 1972 : CUS Verona\n* 1973 : C.S. Esercito Roma\n* 1974 : HC Rovereto\n* 1975 : HC Rovereto <small>(2)</small>\n* 1976 : Pallamano Trieste\n* 1977 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(2)</small>\n* 1978 : HC Rovereto <small>(3)</small>\n* 1979 : Pallamano Trieste <small>(3)</small>\n* 1980 : 