road={{jct|state=TX|Toll|SHT}}\n|notes=Interchange\n}}\n{{TXint\n|location=Houston\n|type=incomplete\n|lspan=10\n|mile=268.435\n|road={{jct|state=TX|Beltway|8|name1=Frontage Road|road=West Little York Road / North Gessner Road}}\n|notes=No eastbound exit or westbound entrance, (closed until September 2019)\n}}\n{{TXint\n|type=hov\n|mile=266.408\n|road=West Little York Park & Ride\n|notes=Interchange for 290 Express Lane\n}}\n{{TXint\n|type=incomplete\n|mile=267.776\n|mile2=268.984\n|road=Fairbanks-North Houston Road\n|notes=No westbound entrance (closed until October 2019)\n}}\n{{TXint\n|type=\n|mile=269.347\n|mile2=270.747\n|road=West Tidwell Road / Hollister Road\n|notes=\n}}\n{{TXint\n|mile=270.195\n|mile2=272.467\n|road=Pinemont Drive / Bingle Road / West 43rd Street <!--Bingle and West 43rd each have their own eastbound entrance ramps-->\n|notes=Separate exits for West 43rd & Bingle/Pinemont westbound, opened in October 2017.\n}}\n{{TXint\n|mile=271.927\n|mile2=273.748\n|road=Antoine Drive / West 34th Street\n|notes=\n}}\n{{TXint\n|type=incomplete\n|mile=273.404\n|road={{jct|state=TX|I|10|name1=[[US 90 (TX)|US 90]]<!--not signed-->|city1=San Antonio|location2=[[Downtown Houston|Downtown]]}} <!-- I-10 is now signed-->\n|notes=I-10 exit 763; I-610 exit 11; eastbound exit only.\n}}\n{{TXint\n|type=incomplete\n|mile=273.228\n|mile2=274.185\n|road=Mangum Road / Dacoma Street\n|notes=No eastbound entrance\n}}\n{{TXint\n|type=hov\n|mile_ref=N/A\n|road={{jct|state=TX|I|10|dir1=east|road=Hempstead Road / Katy Road|location1=NW Transit Center|location2=[[Downtown Houston|Downtown]]}}\n|notes=Eastbound exit for 290 Express Lane; east end of HOV/toll lanes at I-10, exit 763.\n}}\n{{TXint\n|road={{jct|state=TX|I|610}}\n|mile=274.372\n|notes=Eastern terminus; I-610 exit 13A; [[directional T interchange|redesigned tri-stack interchange]]. <!--What's going on with construction?-->\n}}\n{{jctbtm|keys=concur,etc,hov,incomplete,closed}}\n\n==Business routes==\nUS&nbsp;290 has three [[business route]]s.\n\n===Brenham===\n{{infobox road small\n|state=TX\n|type=US\n|route=290\n|subtype=BUS\n|name=Business US Highway 290-F\n|location=[[Brenham, Texas|Brenham]]\n|length_mi=4.590\n|length_round=2\n|length_ref=<ref name=\"TxDOT BU 290-F\">{{TxDOT|BU|290|F|accessdate=August 10, 2013}}</ref>\n|formed=1990\n}}\n[[File:Texas Loop 318.svg|50px|left]]\n'''Business U.S. Highway 290-F (Bus. US&nbsp;290)''' is the original routing of US&nbsp;290 through the town of [[Brenham, Texas|Brenham]]. The route is {{convert|4.59|mi|km}} in length. The route was designated as '''Texas State Highway Loop 318''' throughout its entire length on January 18, 1960. On February 28, 1973, the section from then-SH 90 westward became part of SH 105. It was established in 1990 when the mainline of US&nbsp;290 was rerouted along with [[Texas State Highway 36|SH&nbsp;36]] around the western and southern sides of Brenham.<ref name=\"TxDOT BU 290-F\"/> The routing begins to the west of town at an intersection with SH&nbsp;36. The business route continues east into downtown on Main Street. Before reaching downtown, the route splits into two parallel one-way streets: Main Street carrying westbound traffic and Alamo Street carrying eastbound traffic. It passes through downtown, meeting the business routing of State Highway 36 and the western terminus of [[Texas State Highway 105|SH&nbsp;105]]. At this intersection, the business route turns south on Market Street, and continues out of Brenham, rejoining the mainline US&nbsp;290 near an intersection with [[Farm to Market Road 577|FM&nbsp;577]].<ref name=\"Mapbook 452\">{{Texas Mapbook|year=2014|page=452|accessdate=December 3, 2014|link=no}}</ref><ref name=\"Mapbook 453\">{{Texas Mapbook|year=2014|page=453|accessdate=December 3, 2014|link=no}}</ref>{{Clear}}\n\n===Hempstead\u2013Hockley===\n{{infobox road small\n|state=TX\n|type=US\n|route=290\n|subtype=BUS\n|name=Business US Highway 290-H\n|location=[[Hempstead, Texas|Hempstead]]\u2013[[Hockley, Texas|Hockley]]\n|length_mi=16.991\n|length_round=3\n|length_ref=<ref name=\"TxDOT BU 290-H\" />\n|formed=1995\n}}\n'''Business U.S. Highway 290-H (Bus. US&nbsp;290)''' is the original routing of US&nbsp;290 through the towns of [[Hempstead, Texas|Hempstead]], [[Waller, Texas|Waller]], and [[Hockley, Texas|Hockley]].<ref name=\"Mapbook 475\">{{Texas Mapbook|year=2014|page=475|accessdate=December 3, 2014|link=no}}</ref> This route was designated between 1995 and 1998 in stages as a limited-access bypass route was constructed to the north of these towns.<ref name=\"TxDOT BU 290-H\">{{TxDOT|BU|290|H|accessdate=August 10, 2013}}</ref> It begins at the interchange with US&nbsp;290 and SH&nbsp;6 and travels south into Hempstead along 10th Street. At an intersection with [[Texas State Highway 159|SH&nbsp;159]], the business route turns east onto Austin Street and subsequently runs parallel to the adjacent railroad after leaving Hempstead city limits. It intersects several amenities in [[Prairie View, Texas|Prairie View]] before serving downtown Waller while designated as Hempstead Road. After passing through several industrial facilities and serving downtown Hockley, the business route becomes US&nbsp;290's southbound frontage road just prior to the interchange with Badtke Road.{{Clear}}\n\n===Cypress===\n{{infobox road small\n|state=TX\n|type=US\n|route=290\n|subtype=BUS\n|name=Business US Highway 290-L\n|location=[[Cypress, Texas|Cypress]]\n|length_mi=1.396\n|length_round=3\n|length_ref=<ref name=\"TxDOT BU 290-L\" />\n|formed=1993\n}}\n'''Business U.S. Highway 290-L (Bus. US&nbsp;290)''' is the original routing of US&nbsp;290 through the town of [[Cypress, Texas|Cypress]].<ref name=\"Mapbook 496\">{{Texas Mapbook|year=2014|page=496|accessdate=December 3, 2014|link=no}}</ref> The route was designated in 1993 as a limited-access bypass was built to the northeast of the original routing.<ref name=\"TxDOT BU 290-L\">{{TxDOT|BU|290|L|accessdate=August 10, 2013}}</ref> At roughly {{convert|1.3|mi|km}}, it is US&nbsp;290's shortest designated business route, serving the south side of Cypress's shopping area near the Fry Road and Spring Cypress Road interchanges.{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Attached KML|display=title,inline}}\n{{Commons category|U.S. Route 290}}\n*[http://usends.com/290.html Endpoints of U.S. Highway 290]\n\n{{US 90}}\n{{Austin Streets}}\n\n[[Category:United States Numbered Highways|90-2]]\n[[Category:U.S. Highways in Texas|90-2]]\n[[Category:U.S. Route 90|2]]\n[[Category:Interstate 10|290]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Kimble County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Gillespie County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Blanco County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Hays County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Travis County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Bastrop County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Lee County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Fayette County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Washington County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Waller County, Texas]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Harris County, Texas]]\n", "name_user": "ToThAc", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eRoute description", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Route_290"}
